OL,3,CSiege and slaughter: The border town
OL,4,Cwith a bloody role in British history
OL,6,FDerek Sharman MBE is a tour guide in
OL,7,Fthe town and said it "wasn't a place
OL,8,Ffor a quiet life".
OL,10,F"People here on the borders wouldn't
OL,11,Factually consider themselves really
OL,12,FEnglish or Scots, they're Borderer's,"
OL,13,Fhe added.
OL,15,F"What mattered really was who was in
OL,16,Fcharge at the time - you'd just keep
OL,17,Fyour head down and do what they were
OL,18,Ftold to do.
