OL,3,CSiege and slaughter: The border town
OL,4,Cwith a bloody role in British history
OL,6,F"Even when the town was captured by
OL,7,Fsiege and slaughter, people still had
OL,8,Fto be left here to carry on producing
OL,9,Fthe food and doing the things that
OL,10,Fpeople needed so you couldn't kill
OL,11,Feverybody. It wasn't a nice place to
OL,12,Flive in the middle ages."
OL,14,FThe remains of Berwick castle still
OL,15,Fstand in the town today. The fortress
OL,16,Fwas at times home to both English and
OL,17,FScottish royalty.
OL,19,FBuilt by Edward I of England, it was
OL,20,Fonce one of the strongest castles in
OL,21,Fthe North of Britain.
