OL,3,CSiege and slaughter: The border town
OL,4,Cwith a bloody role in British history
OL,6,FMr Sharman continued: "If the French
OL,7,Fhad captured Berwick, the whole of
OL,8,FBritish and European history would be
OL,9,Fvery different.
OL,11,F"If the Scots had held onto Berwick
OL,12,Fthen Scottish history would be very
OL,13,Fdifferent. Who knows what the country
OL,14,Fcould have developed into.
OL,16,F"It's a place people feel very proud
OL,17,Fof because of this history and they
OL,18,Fknow how important it was. It's not as
OL,19,Fimportant today in that sense, but
OL,20,Fit's crucial to the history of the
OL,21,Fcountry."
