OL,3,CSiege and slaughter: The border town
OL,4,Cwith a bloody role in British history
OL,6,FDetermined to keep Berwick in English
OL,7,Fhands, Elizabeth I built a series of
OL,8,Fdefence bastions throughout the town.
OL,10,F"Scots and English had been fighting
OL,11,Ffor nearly 300 years and warfares
OL,12,Fchange," continued Mr Sharman.
OL,14,F"It was the time of artillery and not
OL,15,Fcatapults and people climbing up
OL,16,Fladders. As a result this new state of
OL,17,Fthe art defence system was built.
