OL,4,Cwith a bloody role in British history
OL,6,FAccording to Mr Sharman, the defence
OL,7,Fwalls were considered so impressive
OL,8,Fthat the Scots did not try and attack
OL,9,FBerwick afterwards.
OL,11,FBy 1603 England and Scotland came
OL,12,Ftogether under one king, and since the
OL,13,F1700s an army regiment was based at
OL,14,Fthe Barracks right up to the 1960s.
OL,16,FLocals are extremely proud of the
OL,17,Farea's rich history.
